  nickname: pro
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 51ee3e37f5ded7941ab6216610f6fc67, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: The Purpose of Proverbs
      content: "  These are the proverbs of Solomon, David\u2019s son, king of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their purpose is to teach people wisdom and discipline,to help them
        understand the insights of the wise.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their purpose is to teach people to live disciplined and successful
        lives,to help them do what is right, just, and fair.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These proverbs will give insight to the simple,knowledge and discernment
        to the young.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let the wise listen to these proverbs and become even wiser.Let those
        with understanding receive guidance  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'by exploring the meaning in these proverbs and parables,the words
        of the wise and their riddles.  '
      comments: []
    - title: "A Father\u2019s Exhortation: Acquire Wisdom"
      content: 'Fear of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is the foundation of true
        knowledge,but fools despise wisdom and discipline.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My child,[[COMMENT(0)]] listen when your father corrects you.Don\u2019t
        neglect your mother\u2019s instruction.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:8 '
        content: Hebrew <b>My son; </b>also in 1:10, 15.
    - title: 
      content: 'What you learn from them will crown you with graceand be a chain
        of honor around your neck.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My child, if sinners entice you,turn your back on them!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They may say, \u201CCome and join us.Let\u2019s hide and kill someone!Just
        for fun, let\u2019s ambush the innocent!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Let\u2019s swallow them alive, like the grave[[COMMENT(0)]];let\u2019s
        swallow them whole, like those who go down to the pit of death.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:12 '
        content: Hebrew <b>like Sheol.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Think of the great things we\u2019ll get!We\u2019ll fill our houses
        with all the stuff we take.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Come, throw in your lot with us;we\u2019ll all share the loot.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My child, don\u2019t go along with them!Stay far away from their
        paths.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They rush to commit evil deeds.They hurry to commit murder.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If a bird sees a trap being set,it knows to stay away.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But these people set an ambush for themselves;they are trying to
        get themselves killed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Wisdom Shouts in the Streets
      content: 'Such is the fate of all who are greedy for money;it robs them of
        life.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wisdom shouts in the streets.She cries out in the public square.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She calls to the crowds along the main street,to those gathered in
        front of the city gate:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHow long, you simpletons,will you insist on being simpleminded?How
        long will you mockers relish your mocking?How long will you fools hate knowledge?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Come and listen to my counsel.I\u2019ll share my heart with youand
        make you wise.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI called you so often, but you wouldn\u2019t come.I reached
        out to you, but you paid no attention.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You ignored my adviceand rejected the correction I offered.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So I will laugh when you are in trouble!I will mock you when disaster
        overtakes you\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'when calamity overtakes you like a storm,when disaster engulfs you
        like a cyclone,and anguish and distress overwhelm you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen they cry for help, I will not answer.Though they anxiously
        search for me, they will not find me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For they hated knowledgeand chose not to fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They rejected my adviceand paid no attention when I corrected them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Therefore, they must eat the bitter fruit of living their own way,choking
        on their own schemes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For simpletons turn away from me\u2014to death.Fools are destroyed
        by their own complacency.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Benefits of Wisdom
      content: '  My child,[[COMMENT(0)]] listen to what I say,and treasure my commands.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>My son.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Tune your ears to wisdom,and concentrate on understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Cry out for insight,and ask for understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Search for them as you would for silver;seek them like hidden treasures.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then you will understand what it means to fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and
        you will gain knowledge of God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> grants wisdom!From his mouth
        come knowledge and understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He grants a treasure of common sense to the honest.He is a shield
        to those who walk with integrity.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He guards the paths of the justand protects those who are faithful
        to him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then you will understand what is right, just, and fair,and you will
        find the right way to go.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For wisdom will enter your heart,and knowledge will fill you with
        joy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wise choices will watch over you.Understanding will keep you safe.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wisdom will save you from evil people,from those whose words are
        twisted.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These men turn from the right wayto walk down dark paths.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They take pleasure in doing wrong,and they enjoy the twisted ways
        of evil.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their actions are crooked,and their ways are wrong.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wisdom will save you from the immoral woman,from the seductive words
        of the promiscuous woman.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She has abandoned her husbandand ignores the covenant she made before
        God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Entering her house leads to death;it is the road to the grave.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:18 '
        content: Hebrew <b>to the spirits of the dead.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The man who visits her is doomed.He will never reach the paths of
        life.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So follow the steps of the good,and stay on the paths of the righteous.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For only the godly will live in the land,and those with integrity
        will remain in it.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Trusting in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
      content: '  My child,[[COMMENT(0)]] never forget the things I have taught you.Store
        my commands in your heart.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>My son; </b>also in 3:11, 21.
    - title: 
      content: 'If you do this, you will live many years,and your life will be satisfying.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Never let loyalty and kindness leave you!Tie them around your neck
        as a reminder.Write them deep within your heart.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then you will find favor with both God and people,and you will earn
        a good reputation.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Trust in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> with all your heart;do not
        depend on your own understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Seek his will in all you do,and he will show you which path to take.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t be impressed with your own wisdom.Instead, fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and turn away from evil.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then you will have healing for your bodyand strength for your bones.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Honor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> with your wealthand with the
        best part of everything you produce.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then he will fill your barns with grain,and your vats will overflow
        with good wine.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My child, don\u2019t reject the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        discipline,and don\u2019t be upset when he corrects you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> corrects those he loves,just
        as a father corrects a child in whom he delights.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:12 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>loves, / and he punishes those he accepts
          as his children. </b>Compare Heb 12:6.
    - title: 
      content: 'Joyful is the person who finds wisdom,the one who gains understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For wisdom is more profitable than silver,and her wages are better
        than gold.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wisdom is more precious than rubies;nothing you desire can compare
        with her.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She offers you long life in her right hand,and riches and honor in
        her left.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She will guide you down delightful paths;all her ways are satisfying.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wisdom is a tree of life to those who embrace her;happy are those
        who hold her tightly.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'By wisdom the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> founded the earth;by understanding
        he created the heavens.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'By his knowledge the deep fountains of the earth burst forth,and
        the dew settles beneath the night sky.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My child, don\u2019t lose sight of common sense and discernment.Hang
        on to them,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'for they will refresh your soul.They are like jewels on a necklace.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They keep you safe on your way,and your feet will not stumble.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You can go to bed without fear;you will lie down and sleep soundly.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You need not be afraid of sudden disasteror the destruction that
        comes upon the wicked,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is your security.He will keep
        your foot from being caught in a trap.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Do not withhold good from those who deserve itwhen it\u2019s in your
        power to help them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If you can help your neighbor now, don\u2019t say,\u201CCome back
        tomorrow, and then I\u2019ll help you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t plot harm against your neighbor,for those who live nearby
        trust you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t pick a fight without reason,when no one has done you harm.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t envy violent peopleor copy their ways.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Such wicked people are detestable to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,but
        he offers his friendship to the godly.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> curses the house of the wicked,but
        he blesses the home of the upright.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> mocks the mockersbut is gracious
        to the humble.[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>Compare Jas 4:6; 1 Pet 5:5.</smallcaps>  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:34 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>The <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>
          opposes the proud / but gives grace to the humble. </b>
  - verses:
    - title: "A Father\u2019s Wise Advice"
      content: '  My children,[[COMMENT(0)]] listen when your father corrects you.Pay
        attention and learn good judgment,  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>My sons.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "for I am giving you good guidance.Don\u2019t turn away from my instructions.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I, too, was once my father\u2019s son,tenderly loved as my mother\u2019s
        only child.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My father taught me,\u201CTake my words to heart.Follow my commands,
        and you will live.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Get wisdom; develop good judgment.Don\u2019t forget my words or turn
        away from them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t turn your back on wisdom, for she will protect you.Love
        her, and she will guard you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Getting wisdom is the wisest thing you can do!And whatever else you
        do, develop good judgment.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you prize wisdom, she will make you great.Embrace her, and she
        will honor you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She will place a lovely wreath on your head;she will present you
        with a beautiful crown.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My child,[[COMMENT(0)]] listen to me and do as I say,and you will
        have a long, good life.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:10 '
        content: Hebrew <b>My son; </b>also in 4:20.
    - title: 
      content: "I will teach you wisdom\u2019s waysand lead you in straight paths.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When you walk, you won\u2019t be held back;when you run, you won\u2019t
        stumble.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Take hold of my instructions; don\u2019t let them go.Guard them,
        for they are the key to life.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t do as the wicked do,and don\u2019t follow the path of
        evildoers.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t even think about it; don\u2019t go that way.Turn away
        and keep moving.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For evil people can\u2019t sleep until they\u2019ve done their evil
        deed for the day.They can\u2019t rest until they\u2019ve caused someone to
        stumble.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They eat the food of wickednessand drink the wine of violence!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The way of the righteous is like the first gleam of dawn,which shines
        ever brighter until the full light of day.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the way of the wicked is like total darkness.They have no idea
        what they are stumbling over.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My child, pay attention to what I say.Listen carefully to my words.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t lose sight of them.Let them penetrate deep into your heart,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'for they bring life to those who find them,and healing to their whole
        body.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Guard your heart above all else,for it determines the course of your
        life.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Avoid all perverse talk;stay away from corrupt speech.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Look straight ahead,and fix your eyes on what lies before you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Mark out a straight path for your feet;stay on the safe path.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Avoid Immoral Women
      content: '  My son, pay attention to my wisdom;listen carefully to my wise
        counsel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then you will show discernment,and your lips will express what you\u2019ve
        learned.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the lips of an immoral woman are as sweet as honey,and her mouth
        is smoother than oil.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But in the end she is as bitter as poison,as dangerous as a double-edged
        sword.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Her feet go down to death;her steps lead straight to the grave.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:5 '
        content: Hebrew <b>to Sheol.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "For she cares nothing about the path to life.She staggers down a
        crooked trail and doesn\u2019t realize it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So now, my sons, listen to me.Never stray from what I am about to
        say:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Stay away from her!Don\u2019t go near the door of her house!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you do, you will lose your honorand will lose to merciless people
        all you have achieved.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Strangers will consume your wealth,and someone else will enjoy the
        fruit of your labor.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In the end you will groan in anguishwhen disease consumes your body.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will say, \u201CHow I hated discipline!If only I had not ignored
        all the warnings!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Oh, why didn\u2019t I listen to my teachers?Why didn\u2019t I pay
        attention to my instructors?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have come to the brink of utter ruin,and now I must face public
        disgrace.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Drink water from your own well\u2014share your love only with your
        wife.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:15 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Drink water from your own cistern, / flowing water from
          your own well.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Why spill the water of your springs in the streets,having sex with
        just anyone?[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:16 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Why spill your springs in the streets, / your streams
          in the city squares?</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'You should reserve it for yourselves.Never share it with strangers.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let your wife be a fountain of blessing for you.Rejoice in the wife
        of your youth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She is a loving deer, a graceful doe.Let her breasts satisfy you
        always.May you always be captivated by her love.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Why be captivated, my son, by an immoral woman,or fondle the breasts
        of a promiscuous woman?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sees clearly what a man does,examining
        every path he takes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'An evil man is held captive by his own sins;they are ropes that catch
        and hold him.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Lessons for Daily Life
      content: "  My child,[[COMMENT(0)]] if you have put up security for a friend\u2019s
        debtor agreed to guarantee the debt of a stranger\u2014  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>My son.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "if you have trapped yourself by your agreementand are caught by what
        you said\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "follow my advice and save yourself,for you have placed yourself at
        your friend\u2019s mercy.Now swallow your pride;go and beg to have your name
        erased.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t put it off; do it now!Don\u2019t rest until you do.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Save yourself like a gazelle escaping from a hunter,like a bird fleeing
        from a net.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Take a lesson from the ants, you lazybones.Learn from their ways
        and become wise!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Though they have no princeor governor or ruler to make them work,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'they labor hard all summer,gathering food for the winter.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you, lazybones, how long will you sleep?When will you wake up?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A little extra sleep, a little more slumber,a little folding of the
        hands to rest\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'then poverty will pounce on you like a bandit;scarcity will attack
        you like an armed robber.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What are worthless and wicked people like?They are constant liars,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'signaling their deceit with a wink of the eye,a nudge of the foot,
        or the wiggle of fingers.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their perverted hearts plot evil,and they constantly stir up trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But they will be destroyed suddenly,broken in an instant beyond all
        hope of healing.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There are six things the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> hates\u2014no,
        seven things he detests:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'haughty eyes,a lying tongue,hands that kill the innocent,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'a heart that plots evil,feet that race to do wrong,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'a false witness who pours out lies,a person who sows discord in a
        family.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My son, obey your father\u2019s commands,and don\u2019t neglect your
        mother\u2019s instruction.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Keep their words always in your heart.Tie them around your neck.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When you walk, their counsel will lead you.When you sleep, they will
        protect you.When you wake up, they will advise you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For their command is a lampand their instruction a light;their corrective
        disciplineis the way to life.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It will keep you from the immoral woman,from the smooth tongue of
        a promiscuous woman.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t lust for her beauty.Don\u2019t let her coy glances seduce
        you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For a prostitute will bring you to poverty,[[COMMENT(0)]]but sleeping
        with another man\u2019s wife will cost you your life.  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:26 '
        content: Hebrew <b>to a loaf of bread.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Can a man scoop a flame into his lapand not have his clothes catch
        on fire?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Can he walk on hot coalsand not blister his feet?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So it is with the man who sleeps with another man\u2019s wife.He
        who embraces her will not go unpunished.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Excuses might be found for a thiefwho steals because he is starving.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But if he is caught, he must pay back seven times what he stole,even
        if he has to sell everything in his house.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the man who commits adultery is an utter fool,for he destroys
        himself.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will be wounded and disgraced.His shame will never be erased.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the woman\u2019s jealous husband will be furious,and he will
        show no mercy when he takes revenge.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Another Warning about Immoral Women
      content: '  Follow my advice, my son;always treasure my commands.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Obey my commands and live!Guard my instructions as you guard your
        own eyes.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:2 '
        content: Hebrew <b>as the pupil of your eye.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Tie them on your fingers as a reminder.Write them deep within your
        heart.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Love wisdom like a sister;make insight a beloved member of your family.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let them protect you from an affair with an immoral woman,from listening
        to the flattery of a promiscuous woman.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'While I was at the window of my house,looking through the curtain,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I saw some naive young men,and one in particular who lacked common
        sense.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He was crossing the street near the house of an immoral woman,strolling
        down the path by her house.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It was at twilight, in the evening,as deep darkness fell.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The woman approached him,seductively dressed and sly of heart.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She was the brash, rebellious type,never content to stay at home.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She is often in the streets and markets,soliciting at every corner.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She threw her arms around him and kissed him,and with a brazen look
        she said,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI\u2019ve just made my peace offeringsand fulfilled my vows.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You\u2019re the one I was looking for!I came out to find you, and
        here you are!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My bed is spread with beautiful blankets,with colored sheets of Egyptian
        linen.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I\u2019ve perfumed my bedwith myrrh, aloes, and cinnamon.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Come, let\u2019s drink our fill of love until morning.Let\u2019s
        enjoy each other\u2019s caresses,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "for my husband is not home.He\u2019s away on a long trip.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He has taken a wallet full of money with himand won\u2019t return
        until later this month.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:20 '
        content: Hebrew <b>until the moon is full.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'So she seduced him with her pretty speechand enticed him with her
        flattery.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He followed her at once,like an ox going to the slaughter.He was
        like a stag caught in a trap,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:22 '
        content: As in Greek and Syriac versions; Hebrew reads <b>slaughter, as shackles
          are for the discipline of a fool.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'awaiting the arrow that would pierce its heart.He was like a bird
        flying into a snare,little knowing it would cost him his life.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So listen to me, my sons,and pay attention to my words.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t let your hearts stray away toward her.Don\u2019t wander
        down her wayward path.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For she has been the ruin of many;many men have been her victims.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Wisdom Calls for a Hearing
      content: '  Listen as Wisdom calls out!Hear as understanding raises her voice!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'On the hilltop along the road,she takes her stand at the crossroads.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'By the gates at the entrance to the town,on the road leading in,
        she cries aloud,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI call to you, to all of you!I raise my voice to all people.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You simple people, use good judgment.You foolish people, show some
        understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Listen to me! For I have important things to tell you.Everything
        I say is right,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'for I speak the truthand detest every kind of deception.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My advice is wholesome.There is nothing devious or crooked in it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My words are plain to anyone with understanding,clear to those with
        knowledge.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Choose my instruction rather than silver,and knowledge rather than
        pure gold.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For wisdom is far more valuable than rubies.Nothing you desire can
        compare with it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI, Wisdom, live together with good judgment.I know where to
        discover knowledge and discernment.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All who fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will hate evil.Therefore,
        I hate pride and arrogance,corruption and perverse speech.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Common sense and success belong to me.Insight and strength are mine.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Because of me, kings reign,and rulers make just decrees.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Rulers lead with my help,and nobles make righteous judgments.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:16 '
        content: Some Hebrew manuscripts and Greek version read <b>and nobles are
          judges over the earth.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI love all who love me.Those who search will surely find me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have riches and honor,as well as enduring wealth and justice.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My gifts are better than gold, even the purest gold,my wages better
        than sterling silver!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I walk in righteousness,in paths of justice.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who love me inherit wealth.I will fill their treasuries.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> formed me from the beginning,before
        he created anything else.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I was appointed in ages past,at the very first, before the earth
        began.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I was born before the oceans were created,before the springs bubbled
        forth their waters.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Before the mountains were formed,before the hills, I was born\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'before he had made the earth and fieldsand the first handfuls of
        soil.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I was there when he established the heavens,when he drew the horizon
        on the oceans.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I was there when he set the clouds above,when he established springs
        deep in the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I was there when he set the limits of the seas,so they would not
        spread beyond their boundaries.And when he marked off the earth\u2019s foundations,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I was the architect at his side.I was his constant delight,rejoicing
        always in his presence.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And how happy I was with the world he created;how I rejoiced with
        the human family!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd so, my children,[[COMMENT(0)]] listen to me,for all who
        follow my ways are joyful.  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:32 '
        content: Hebrew <b>my sons.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Listen to my instruction and be wise.Don\u2019t ignore it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Joyful are those who listen to me,watching for me daily at my gates,waiting
        for me outside my home!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For whoever finds me finds lifeand receives favor from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  Wisdom has built her house;she has carved its seven columns.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She has prepared a great banquet,mixed the wines, and set the table.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She has sent her servants to invite everyone to come.She calls out
        from the heights overlooking the city.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCome in with me,\u201D she urges the simple.To those who lack
        good judgment, she says,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCome, eat my food,and drink the wine I have mixed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Leave your simple ways behind, and begin to live;learn to use good
        judgment.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Anyone who rebukes a mocker will get an insult in return.Anyone who
        corrects the wicked will get hurt.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So don\u2019t bother correcting mockers;they will only hate you.But
        correct the wise,and they will love you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Instruct the wise,and they will be even wiser.Teach the righteous,and
        they will learn even more.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Fear of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is the foundation of wisdom.Knowledge
        of the Holy One results in good judgment.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wisdom will multiply your daysand add years to your life.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Folly Calls for a Hearing
      content: 'If you become wise, you will be the one to benefit.If you scorn wisdom,
        you will be the one to suffer.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The woman named Folly is brash.She is ignorant and doesn\u2019t know
        it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She sits in her doorwayon the heights overlooking the city.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She calls out to men going bywho are minding their own business.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCome in with me,\u201D she urges the simple.To those who lack
        good judgment, she says,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CStolen water is refreshing;food eaten in secret tastes the
        best!\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Proverbs of Solomon
      content: '  The proverbs of Solomon:A wise child[[COMMENT(0)]] brings joy to
        a father;a foolish child brings grief to a mother.  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>son; </b>also in 10:1b.
    - title: 
      content: 'Tainted wealth has no lasting value,but right living can save your
        life.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will not let the godly go hungry,but
        he refuses to satisfy the craving of the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Lazy people are soon poor;hard workers get rich.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A wise youth harvests in the summer,but one who sleeps during harvest
        is a disgrace.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The godly are showered with blessings;the words of the wicked conceal
        violent intentions.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We have happy memories of the godly,but the name of a wicked person
        rots away.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The wise are glad to be instructed,but babbling fools fall flat on
        their faces.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'People with integrity walk safely,but those who follow crooked paths
        will be exposed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'People who wink at wrong cause trouble,but a bold reproof promotes
        peace.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:10 '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>but babbling fools fall flat
          on their faces.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The words of the godly are a life-giving fountain;the words of the
        wicked conceal violent intentions.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Hatred stirs up quarrels,but love makes up for all offenses.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wise words come from the lips of people with understanding,but those
        lacking sense will be beaten with a rod.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wise people treasure knowledge,but the babbling of a fool invites
        disaster.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The wealth of the rich is their fortress;the poverty of the poor
        is their destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The earnings of the godly enhance their lives,but evil people squander
        their money on sin.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'People who accept discipline are on the pathway to life,but those
        who ignore correction will go astray.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Hiding hatred makes you a liar;slandering others makes you a fool.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Too much talk leads to sin.Be sensible and keep your mouth shut.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The words of the godly are like sterling silver;the heart of a fool
        is worthless.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The words of the godly encourage many,but fools are destroyed by
        their lack of common sense.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The blessing of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> makes a person rich,and
        he adds no sorrow with it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Doing wrong is fun for a fool,but living wisely brings pleasure to
        the sensible.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The fears of the wicked will be fulfilled;the hopes of the godly
        will be granted.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the storms of life come, the wicked are whirled away,but the
        godly have a lasting foundation.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Lazy people irritate their employers,like vinegar to the teeth or
        smoke in the eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Fear of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lengthens one\u2019s life,but
        the years of the wicked are cut short.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The hopes of the godly result in happiness,but the expectations of
        the wicked come to nothing.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The way of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is a stronghold to those
        with integrity,but it destroys the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The godly will never be disturbed,but the wicked will be removed
        from the land.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The mouth of the godly person gives wise advice,but the tongue that
        deceives will be cut off.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> detests the use of dishonest scales,but
        he delights in accurate weights.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Pride leads to disgrace,but with humility comes wisdom.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Honesty guides good people;dishonesty destroys treacherous people.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Riches won\u2019t help on the day of judgment,but right living can
        save you from death.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The godly are directed by honesty;the wicked fall beneath their load
        of sin.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The godliness of good people rescues them;the ambition of treacherous
        people traps them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the wicked die, their hopes die with them,for they rely on their
        own feeble strength.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The godly are rescued from trouble,and it falls on the wicked instead.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'With their words, the godless destroy their friends,but knowledge
        will rescue the righteous.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The whole city celebrates when the godly succeed;they shout for joy
        when the wicked die.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Upright citizens are good for a city and make it prosper,but the
        talk of the wicked tears it apart.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It is foolish to belittle one\u2019s neighbor;a sensible person keeps
        quiet.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A gossip goes around telling secrets,but those who are trustworthy
        can keep a confidence.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Without wise leadership, a nation falls;there is safety in having
        many advisers.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There\u2019s danger in putting up security for a stranger\u2019s
        debt;it\u2019s safer not to guarantee another person\u2019s debt.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A gracious woman gains respect,but ruthless men gain only wealth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your kindness will reward you,but your cruelty will destroy you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Evil people get rich for the moment,but the reward of the godly will
        last.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Godly people find life;evil people find death.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> detests people with crooked hearts,but
        he delights in those with integrity.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Evil people will surely be punished,but the children of the godly
        will go free.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A beautiful woman who lacks discretionis like a gold ring in a pig\u2019s
        snout.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The godly can look forward to a reward,while the wicked can expect
        only judgment.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Give freely and become more wealthy;be stingy and lose everything.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The generous will prosper;those who refresh others will themselves
        be refreshed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'People curse those who hoard their grain,but they bless the one who
        sells in time of need.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you search for good, you will find favor;but if you search for
        evil, it will find you!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Trust in your money and down you go!But the godly flourish like leaves
        in spring.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who bring trouble on their families inherit the wind.The fool
        will be a servant to the wise.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The seeds of good deeds become a tree of life;a wise person wins
        friends.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:30 '
        content: Or <b>and those who win souls are wise.</b>
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  To learn, you must love discipline;it is stupid to hate correction.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> approves of those who are good,but
        he condemns those who plan wickedness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wickedness never brings stability,but the godly have deep roots.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A worthy wife is a crown for her husband,but a disgraceful woman
        is like cancer in his bones.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The plans of the godly are just;the advice of the wicked is treacherous.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The words of the wicked are like a murderous ambush,but the words
        of the godly save lives.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The wicked die and disappear,but the family of the godly stands firm.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A sensible person wins admiration,but a warped mind is despised.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Better to be an ordinary person with a servantthan to be self-important
        but have no food.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The godly care for their animals,but the wicked are always cruel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A hard worker has plenty of food,but a person who chases fantasies
        has no sense.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Thieves are jealous of each other\u2019s loot,but the godly are well
        rooted and bear their own fruit.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The wicked are trapped by their own words,but the godly escape such
        trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wise words bring many benefits,and hard work brings rewards.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Fools think their own way is right,but the wise listen to others.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A fool is quick-tempered,but a wise person stays calm when insulted.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'An honest witness tells the truth;a false witness tells lies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Some people make cutting remarks,but the words of the wise bring
        healing.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Truthful words stand the test of time,but lies are soon exposed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Deceit fills hearts that are plotting evil;joy fills hearts that
        are planning peace!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No harm comes to the godly,but the wicked have their fill of trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> detests lying lips,but he delights
        in those who tell the truth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The wise don\u2019t make a show of their knowledge,but fools broadcast
        their foolishness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Work hard and become a leader;be lazy and become a slave.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Worry weighs a person down;an encouraging word cheers a person up.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The godly give good advice to their friends;[[COMMENT(0)]]the wicked
        lead them astray.  '
      comments:
      - number: '12:26 '
        content: Or <b>The godly are cautious in friendship; </b>or <b>The godly
          are freed from evil. </b>The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - title: 
      content: "Lazy people don\u2019t even cook the game they catch,but the diligent
        make use of everything they find.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "  A wise child accepts a parent\u2019s discipline;[[COMMENT(0)]]a
        mocker refuses to listen to correction.  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:1 '
        content: "Hebrew <b>A wise son accepts his father\u2019s discipline.</b>"
    - title: 
      content: 'Wise words will win you a good meal,but treacherous people have an
        appetite for violence.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who control their tongue will have a long life;opening your
        mouth can ruin everything.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Lazy people want much but get little,but those who work hard will
        prosper.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The godly hate lies;the wicked cause shame and disgrace.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Godliness guards the path of the blameless,but the evil are misled
        by sin.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Some who are poor pretend to be rich;others who are rich pretend
        to be poor.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The rich can pay a ransom for their lives,but the poor won\u2019t
        even get threatened.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The life of the godly is full of light and joy,but the light of the
        wicked will be snuffed out.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Pride leads to conflict;those who take advice are wise.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wealth from get-rich-quick schemes quickly disappears;wealth from
        hard work grows over time.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Hope deferred makes the heart sick,but a dream fulfilled is a tree
        of life.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'People who despise advice are asking for trouble;those who respect
        a command will succeed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The instruction of the wise is like a life-giving fountain;those
        who accept it avoid the snares of death.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A person with good sense is respected;a treacherous person is headed
        for destruction.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:15 '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>the way of the treacherous
          is lasting.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Wise people think before they act;fools don\u2019t\u2014and even
        brag about their foolishness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'An unreliable messenger stumbles into trouble,but a reliable messenger
        brings healing.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you ignore criticism, you will end in poverty and disgrace;if
        you accept correction, you will be honored.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It is pleasant to see dreams come true,but fools refuse to turn from
        evil to attain them.  '
