      content: 'Though good advice lies deep within the heart,a person with understanding
        will draw it out.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Many will say they are loyal friends,but who can find one who is
        truly reliable?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The godly walk with integrity;blessed are their children who follow
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When a king sits in judgment, he weighs all the evidence,distinguishing
        the bad from the good.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who can say, \u201CI have cleansed my heart;I am pure and free from
        sin\u201D?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "False weights and unequal measures[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        detests double standards of every kind.  "
      comments:
      - number: '20:10 '
        content: Hebrew <b>A stone and a stone, an ephah and an ephah.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Even children are known by the way they act,whether their conduct
        is pure, and whether it is right.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Ears to hear and eyes to see\u2014both are gifts from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you love sleep, you will end in poverty.Keep your eyes open, and
        there will be plenty to eat!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The buyer haggles over the price, saying, \u201CIt\u2019s worthless,\u201Dthen
        brags about getting a bargain!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wise words are more valuablethan much gold and many rubies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Get security from someone who guarantees a stranger\u2019s debt.Get
        a deposit if he does it for foreigners.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '20:16 '
        content: An alternate reading in the Masoretic Text is <b>for a promiscuous
          woman.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Stolen bread tastes sweet,but it turns to gravel in the mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Plans succeed through good counsel;don\u2019t go to war without wise
        advice.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A gossip goes around telling secrets,so don\u2019t hang around with
        chatterers.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you insult your father or mother,your light will be snuffed out
        in total darkness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'An inheritance obtained too early in lifeis not a blessing in the
        end.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t say, \u201CI will get even for this wrong.\u201DWait for
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to handle the matter.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> detests double standards;he is not
        pleased by dishonest scales.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> directs our steps,so why try to understand
        everything along the way?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t trap yourself by making a rash promise to Godand only
        later counting the cost.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A wise king scatters the wicked like wheat,then runs his threshing
        wheel over them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s light penetrates the human
        spirit,[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>exposing every hidden motive.</smallcaps>  "
      comments:
      - number: '20:27 '
        content: "Or <b>The human spirit is the <span class=\"ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf\">Lord</span>\u2019s
          light.</b>"
    - title: 
      content: 'Unfailing love and faithfulness protect the king;his throne is made
        secure through love.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The glory of the young is their strength;the gray hair of experience
        is the splendor of the old.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "  The king\u2019s heart is like a stream of water directed by the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;he guides it wherever he pleases.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'People may be right in their own eyes,but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        examines their heart.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is more pleased when we do what is
        right and justthan when we offer him sacrifices.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Haughty eyes, a proud heart,and evil actions are all sin.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Good planning and hard work lead to prosperity,but hasty shortcuts
        lead to poverty.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wealth created by a lying tongueis a vanishing mist and a deadly
        trap.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '21:6 '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>mist for those who seek death.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The violence of the wicked sweeps them away,because they refuse to
        do what is just.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The guilty walk a crooked path;the innocent travel a straight road.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It\u2019s better to live alone in the corner of an atticthan with
        a quarrelsome wife in a lovely home.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Evil people desire evil;their neighbors get no mercy from them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you punish a mocker, the simpleminded become wise;if you instruct
        the wise, they will be all the wiser.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The Righteous One[[COMMENT(0)]] knows what is going on in the homes
        of the wicked;he will bring disaster on them.  '
      comments:
      - number: '21:12 '
        content: Or <b>The righteous man.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who shut their ears to the cries of the poorwill be ignored
        in their own time of need.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A secret gift calms anger;a bribe under the table pacifies fury.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Justice is a joy to the godly,but it terrifies evildoers.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The person who strays from common sensewill end up in the company
        of the dead.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who love pleasure become poor;those who love wine and luxury
        will never be rich.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The wicked are punished in place of the godly,and traitors in place
        of the honest.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It\u2019s better to live alone in the desertthan with a quarrelsome,
        complaining wife.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The wise have wealth and luxury,but fools spend whatever they get.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Whoever pursues righteousness and unfailing lovewill find life, righteousness,
        and honor.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The wise conquer the city of the strongand level the fortress in
        which they trust.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Watch your tongue and keep your mouth shut,and you will stay out
        of trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Mockers are proud and haughty;they act with boundless arrogance.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Despite their desires, the lazy will come to ruin,for their hands
        refuse to work.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Some people are always greedy for more,but the godly love to give!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The sacrifice of an evil person is detestable,especially when it
        is offered with wrong motives.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A false witness will be cut off,but a credible witness will be allowed
        to speak.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The wicked bluff their way through,but the virtuous think before
        they act.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No human wisdom or understanding or plancan stand against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  Choose a good reputation over great riches;being held in high esteem
        is better than silver or gold.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The rich and poor have this in common:The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        made them both.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A prudent person foresees danger and takes precautions.The simpleton
        goes blindly on and suffers the consequences.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'True humility and fear of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>lead to
        riches, honor, and long life.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Corrupt people walk a thorny, treacherous road;whoever values life
        will avoid it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Direct your children onto the right path,and when they are older,
        they will not leave it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Just as the rich rule the poor,so the borrower is servant to the
        lender.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who plant injustice will harvest disaster,and their reign of
        terror will come to an end.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '22:8 '
        content: 'The Greek version includes an additional proverb: <b>God blesses
          a man who gives cheerfully, / but his worthless deeds will come to an end.
          </b>Compare 2 Cor 9:7.'
    - title: 
      content: 'Blessed are those who are generous,because they feed the poor.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Throw out the mocker, and fighting goes, too.Quarrels and insults
        will disappear.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Whoever loves a pure heart and gracious speechwill have the king
        as a friend.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> preserves those with knowledge,but
        he ruins the plans of the treacherous.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The lazy person claims, \u201CThere\u2019s a lion out there!If I
        go outside, I might be killed!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The mouth of an immoral woman is a dangerous trap;those who make
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> angry will fall into it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A youngster\u2019s heart is filled with foolishness,but physical
        discipline will drive it far away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Sayings of the Wise
      content: 'A person who gets ahead by oppressing the pooror by showering gifts
        on the rich will end in poverty.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Listen to the words of the wise;apply your heart to my instruction.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For it is good to keep these sayings in your heartand always ready
        on your lips.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I am teaching you today\u2014yes, you\u2014so you will trust in the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have written thirty sayings[[COMMENT(0)]] for you,filled with advice
        and knowledge.  '
      comments:
      - number: '22:20 '
        content: Or <b>excellent sayings; </b>the meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - title: 
      content: 'In this way, you may know the truthand take an accurate report to
        those who sent you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t rob the poor just because you can,or exploit the needy
        in court.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is their defender.He will ruin
        anyone who ruins them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t befriend angry peopleor associate with hot-tempered people,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'or you will learn to be like themand endanger your soul.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t agree to guarantee another person\u2019s debtor put up
        security for someone else.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If you can\u2019t pay it,even your bed will be snatched from under
        you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t cheat your neighbor by moving the ancient boundary markersset
        up by previous generations.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  While dining with a ruler,pay attention to what is put before you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you are a big eater,put a knife to your throat;  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "don\u2019t desire all the delicacies,for he might be trying to trick
        you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t wear yourself out trying to get rich.Be wise enough to
        know when to quit.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In the blink of an eye wealth disappears,for it will sprout wingsand
        fly away like an eagle.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t eat with people who are stingy;don\u2019t desire their
        delicacies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They are always thinking about how much it costs.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201CEat
        and drink,\u201D they say, but they don\u2019t mean it.  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:7 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - title: 
      content: "You will throw up what little you\u2019ve eaten,and your compliments
        will be wasted.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t waste your breath on fools,for they will despise the wisest
        advice.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t cheat your neighbor by moving the ancient boundary markers;don\u2019t
        take the land of defenseless orphans.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For their Redeemer[[COMMENT(0)]] is strong;he himself will bring
        their charges against you.  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:11 '
        content: Or <b>redeemer.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Commit yourself to instruction;listen carefully to words of knowledge.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t fail to discipline your children.The rod of punishment
        won\u2019t kill them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Physical disciplinemay well save them from death.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:14 '
        content: Hebrew <b>from Sheol.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'My child,[[COMMENT(0)]] if your heart is wise,my own heart will rejoice!  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:15 '
        content: Hebrew <b>My son; </b>also in 23:19.
    - title: 
      content: 'Everything in me will celebratewhen you speak what is right.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t envy sinners,but always continue to fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will be rewarded for this;your hope will not be disappointed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My child, listen and be wise:Keep your heart on the right course.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do not carouse with drunkardsor feast with gluttons,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'for they are on their way to poverty,and too much sleep clothes them
        in rags.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Listen to your father, who gave you life,and don\u2019t despise your
        mother when she is old.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Get the truth and never sell it;also get wisdom, discipline, and
        good judgment.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The father of godly children has cause for joy.What a pleasure to
        have children who are wise.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:24 '
        content: Hebrew <b>to have a wise son.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'So give your father and mother joy!May she who gave you birth be
        happy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O my son, give me your heart.May your eyes take delight in following
        my ways.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A prostitute is a dangerous trap;a promiscuous woman is as dangerous
        as falling into a narrow well.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She hides and waits like a robber,eager to make more men unfaithful.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who has anguish? Who has sorrow?Who is always fighting? Who is always
        complaining?Who has unnecessary bruises? Who has bloodshot eyes?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It is the one who spends long hours in the taverns,trying out new
        drinks.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t gaze at the wine, seeing how red it is,how it sparkles
        in the cup, how smoothly it goes down.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For in the end it bites like a poisonous snake;it stings like a viper.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will see hallucinations,and you will say crazy things.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will stagger like a sailor tossed at sea,clinging to a swaying
        mast.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "  Don\u2019t envy evil peopleor desire their company.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For their hearts plot violence,and their words always stir up trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A house is built by wisdomand becomes strong through good sense.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Through knowledge its rooms are filledwith all sorts of precious
        riches and valuables.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The wise are mightier than the strong,[[COMMENT(0)]]and those with
        knowledge grow stronger and stronger.  '
      comments:
      - number: '24:5 '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>A wise man is strength.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "So don\u2019t go to war without wise guidance;victory depends on
        having many advisers.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wisdom is too lofty for fools.Among leaders at the city gate, they
        have nothing to say.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A person who plans evilwill get a reputation as a troublemaker.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The schemes of a fool are sinful;everyone detests a mocker.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you fail under pressure,your strength is too small.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Rescue those who are unjustly sentenced to die;save them as they
        stagger to their death.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t excuse yourself by saying, \u201CLook, we didn\u2019t
        know.\u201DFor God understands all hearts, and he sees you.He who guards
        your soul knows you knew.He will repay all people as their actions deserve.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My child,[[COMMENT(0)]] eat honey, for it is good,and the honeycomb
        is sweet to the taste.  '
      comments:
      - number: '24:13 '
        content: Hebrew <b>My son; </b>also in 24:21.
    - title: 
      content: 'In the same way, wisdom is sweet to your soul.If you find it, you
        will have a bright future,and your hopes will not be cut short.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t wait in ambush at the home of the godly,and don\u2019t
        raid the house where the godly live.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The godly may trip seven times, but they will get up again.But one
        disaster is enough to overthrow the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t rejoice when your enemies fall;don\u2019t be happy when
        they stumble.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be displeased with youand
        will turn his anger away from them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t fret because of evildoers;don\u2019t envy the wicked.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For evil people have no future;the light of the wicked will be snuffed
        out.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My child, fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and the king.Don\u2019t
        associate with rebels,  "
      comments: []
    - title: More Sayings of the Wise
      content: 'for disaster will hit them suddenly.Who knows what punishment will
        comefrom the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and the king?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Here are some further sayings of the wise:It is wrong to show favoritism
        when passing judgment.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A judge who says to the wicked, \u201CYou are innocent,\u201Dwill
        be cursed by many people and denounced by the nations.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But it will go well for those who convict the guilty;rich blessings
        will be showered on them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'An honest answeris like a kiss of friendship.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do your planning and prepare your fieldsbefore building your house.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t testify against your neighbors without cause;don\u2019t
        lie about them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And don\u2019t say, \u201CNow I can pay them back for what they\u2019ve
        done to me!I\u2019ll get even with them!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I walked by the field of a lazy person,the vineyard of one with no
        common sense.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I saw that it was overgrown with nettles.It was covered with weeds,and
        its walls were broken down.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then, as I looked and thought about it,I learned this lesson:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A little extra sleep, a little more slumber,a little folding of the
        hands to rest\u2014  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: More Proverbs of Solomon
      content: '  These are more proverbs of Solomon, collected by the advisers of
        King Hezekiah of Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It is God\u2019s privilege to conceal thingsand the king\u2019s privilege
        to discover them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No one can comprehend the height of heaven, the depth of the earth,or
        all that goes on in the king\u2019s mind!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Remove the impurities from silver,and the sterling will be ready
        for the silversmith.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Remove the wicked from the king\u2019s court,and his reign will be
        made secure by justice.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t demand an audience with the kingor push for a place among
        the great.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It\u2019s better to wait for an invitation to the head tablethan
        to be sent away in public disgrace.Just because you\u2019ve seen something,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "don\u2019t be in a hurry to go to court.For what will you do in the
        endif your neighbor deals you a shameful defeat?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When arguing with your neighbor,don\u2019t betray another person\u2019s
        secret.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Others may accuse you of gossip,and you will never regain your good
        reputation.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Timely advice is lovely,like golden apples in a silver basket.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'To one who listens, valid criticismis like a gold earring or other
        gold jewelry.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Trustworthy messengers refresh like snow in summer.They revive the
        spirit of their employer.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A person who promises a gift but doesn\u2019t give itis like clouds
        and wind that bring no rain.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Patience can persuade a prince,and soft speech can break bones.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Do you like honey?Don\u2019t eat too much, or it will make you sick!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t visit your neighbors too often,or you will wear out your
        welcome.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Telling lies about othersis as harmful as hitting them with an ax,wounding
        them with a sword,or shooting them with a sharp arrow.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Putting confidence in an unreliable person in times of troubleis
        like chewing with a broken tooth or walking on a lame foot.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Singing cheerful songs to a person with a heavy heartis like taking
        someone\u2019s coat in cold weatheror pouring vinegar in a wound.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '25:20 '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>pouring vinegar on soda.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'If your enemies are hungry, give them food to eat.If they are thirsty,
        give them water to drink.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will heap burning coals of shame on their heads,and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will reward you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As surely as a north wind brings rain,so a gossiping tongue causes
        anger!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It\u2019s better to live alone in the corner of an atticthan with
        a quarrelsome wife in a lovely home.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Good news from far awayis like cold water to the thirsty.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If the godly give in to the wicked,it\u2019s like polluting a fountain
        or muddying a spring.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It\u2019s not good to eat too much honey,and it\u2019s not good to
        seek honors for yourself.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  Honor is no more associated with foolsthan snow with summer or
        rain with harvest.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Like a fluttering sparrow or a darting swallow,an undeserved curse
        will not land on its intended victim.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Guide a horse with a whip, a donkey with a bridle,and a fool with
        a rod to his back!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t answer the foolish arguments of fools,or you will become
        as foolish as they are.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Be sure to answer the foolish arguments of fools,or they will become
        wise in their own estimation.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Trusting a fool to convey a messageis like cutting off one\u2019s
        feet or drinking poison!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A proverb in the mouth of a foolis as useless as a paralyzed leg.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Honoring a foolis as foolish as tying a stone to a slingshot.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A proverb in the mouth of a foolis like a thorny branch brandished
        by a drunk.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'An employer who hires a fool or a bystanderis like an archer who
        shoots at random.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As a dog returns to its vomit,so a fool repeats his foolishness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There is more hope for foolsthan for people who think they are wise.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The lazy person claims, \u201CThere\u2019s a lion on the road!Yes,
        I\u2019m sure there\u2019s a lion out there!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As a door swings back and forth on its hinges,so the lazy person
        turns over in bed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Lazy people take food in their handbut don\u2019t even lift it to
        their mouth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Lazy people consider themselves smarterthan seven wise counselors.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Interfering in someone else\u2019s argumentis as foolish as yanking
        a dog\u2019s ears.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Just as damagingas a madman shooting a deadly weapon  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "is someone who lies to a friendand then says, \u201CI was only joking.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Fire goes out without wood,and quarrels disappear when gossip stops.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A quarrelsome person starts fightsas easily as hot embers light charcoal
        or fire lights wood.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Rumors are dainty morselsthat sink deep into one\u2019s heart.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Smooth[[COMMENT(0)]] words may hide a wicked heart,just as a pretty
        glaze covers a clay pot.  '
      comments:
      - number: '26:23 '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>Burning.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "People may cover their hatred with pleasant words,but they\u2019re
        deceiving you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They pretend to be kind, but don\u2019t believe them.Their hearts
        are full of many evils.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '26:25 '
        content: Hebrew <b>seven evils.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'While their hatred may be concealed by trickery,their wrongdoing
        will be exposed in public.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you set a trap for others,you will get caught in it yourself.If
        you roll a boulder down on others,it will crush you instead.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "  Don\u2019t brag about tomorrow,since you don\u2019t know what the
        day will bring.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Let someone else praise you, not your own mouth\u2014a stranger,
        not your own lips.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A stone is heavy and sand is weighty,but the resentment caused by
        a fool is even heavier.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Anger is cruel, and wrath is like a flood,but jealousy is even more
        dangerous.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'An open rebukeis better than hidden love!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wounds from a sincere friendare better than many kisses from an enemy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A person who is full refuses honey,but even bitter food tastes sweet
        to the hungry.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A person who strays from homeis like a bird that strays from its
        nest.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The heartfelt counsel of a friendis as sweet as perfume and incense.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Never abandon a friend\u2014either yours or your father\u2019s.When
        disaster strikes, you won\u2019t have to ask your brother for assistance.It\u2019s
        better to go to a neighbor than to a brother who lives far away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Be wise, my child,[[COMMENT(0)]] and make my heart glad.Then I will
        be able to answer my critics.  '
      comments:
      - number: '27:11 '
        content: Hebrew <b>my son.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'A prudent person foresees danger and takes precautions.The simpleton
        goes blindly on and suffers the consequences.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Get security from someone who guarantees a stranger\u2019s debt.Get
        a deposit if he does it for foreigners.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '27:13 '
        content: As in Greek and Latin versions (see also 20:16); Hebrew reads <b>for
          a promiscuous woman.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'A loud and cheerful greeting early in the morningwill be taken as
        a curse!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A quarrelsome wife is as annoyingas constant dripping on a rainy
        day.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Stopping her complaints is like trying to stop the windor trying
        to hold something with greased hands.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As iron sharpens iron,so a friend sharpens a friend.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As workers who tend a fig tree are allowed to eat the fruit,so workers
        who protect their employer\u2019s interests will be rewarded.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As a face is reflected in water,so the heart reflects the real person.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Just as Death and Destruction[[COMMENT(0)]] are never satisfied,so
        human desire is never satisfied.  '
      comments:
      - number: '27:20 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Sheol and Abaddon.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Fire tests the purity of silver and gold,but a person is tested by
        being praised.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '27:21 '
        content: Or <b>by flattery.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'You cannot separate fools from their foolishness,even though you
        grind them like grain with mortar and pestle.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Know the state of your flocks,and put your heart into caring for
        your herds,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "for riches don\u2019t last forever,and the crown might not be passed
        to the next generation.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'After the hay is harvested and the new crop appearsand the mountain
        grasses are gathered in,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'your sheep will provide wool for clothing,and your goats will provide
        the price of a field.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  The wicked run away when no one is chasing them,but the godly are
        as bold as lions.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When there is moral rot within a nation, its government topples easily.But
        wise and knowledgeable leaders bring stability.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A poor person who oppresses the pooris like a pounding rain that
        destroys the crops.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'To reject the law is to praise the wicked;to obey the law is to fight
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Evil people don\u2019t understand justice,but those who follow the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> understand completely.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Better to be poor and honestthan to be dishonest and rich.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Young people who obey the law are wise;those with wild friends bring
        shame to their parents.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '28:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>their father.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Income from charging high interest rateswill end up in the pocket
        of someone who is kind to the poor.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God detests the prayersof a person who ignores the law.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who lead good people along an evil pathwill fall into their
        own trap,but the honest will inherit good things.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Rich people may think they are wise,but a poor person with discernment
        can see right through them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the godly succeed, everyone is glad.When the wicked take charge,
        people go into hiding.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'People who conceal their sins will not prosper,but if they confess
        and turn from them, they will receive mercy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Blessed are those who fear to do wrong,[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>Hebrew
        reads </smallcaps>but the stubborn are headed for serious trouble.  '
      comments:
      - number: '28:14 '
        content: Or <b>those who fear the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>;
          </b><b>those who fear.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'A wicked ruler is as dangerous to the pooras a roaring lion or an
        attacking bear.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A ruler with no understanding will oppress his people,but one who
        hates corruption will have a long life.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A murderer\u2019s tormented conscience will drive him into the grave.Don\u2019t
        protect him!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The blameless will be rescued from harm,but the crooked will be suddenly
        destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A hard worker has plenty of food,but a person who chases fantasies
        ends up in poverty.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The trustworthy person will get a rich reward,but a person who wants
        quick riches will get into trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Showing partiality is never good,yet some will do wrong for a mere
        piece of bread.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Greedy people try to get rich quickbut don\u2019t realize they\u2019re
        headed for poverty.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In the end, people appreciate honest criticismfar more than flattery.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Anyone who steals from his father and motherand says, \u201CWhat\u2019s
        wrong with that?\u201Dis no better than a murderer.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Greed causes fighting;trusting the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> leads
        to prosperity.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who trust their own insight are foolish,but anyone who walks
        in wisdom is safe.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Whoever gives to the poor will lack nothing,but those who close their
        eyes to poverty will be cursed.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  Whoever stubbornly refuses to accept criticismwill suddenly be
        destroyed beyond recovery.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the godly are in authority, the people rejoice.But when the
        wicked are in power, they groan.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The man who loves wisdom brings joy to his father,but if he hangs
        around with prostitutes, his wealth is wasted.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A just king gives stability to his nation,but one who demands bribes
        destroys it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'To flatter friendsis to lay a trap for their feet.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Evil people are trapped by sin,but the righteous escape, shouting
        for joy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The godly care about the rights of the poor;the wicked don\u2019t
        care at all.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Mockers can get a whole town agitated,but the wise will calm anger.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If a wise person takes a fool to court,there will be ranting and
        ridicule but no satisfaction.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The bloodthirsty hate blameless people,but the upright seek to help
        them.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '29:10 '
        content: Or <b>The bloodthirsty hate blameless people, / and they seek to
          kill the upright; </b>Hebrew reads <b>The bloodthirsty hate blameless people;
          / as for the upright, they seek their life.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Fools vent their anger,but the wise quietly hold it back.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If a ruler pays attention to liars,all his advisers will be wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The poor and the oppressor have this in common\u2014the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        gives sight to the eyes of both.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If a king judges the poor fairly,his throne will last forever.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'To discipline a child produces wisdom,but a mother is disgraced by
        an undisciplined child.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the wicked are in authority, sin flourishes,but the godly will
        live to see their downfall.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Discipline your children, and they will give you peace of mindand
        will make your heart glad.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When people do not accept divine guidance, they run wild.But whoever
        obeys the law is joyful.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Words alone will not discipline a servant;the words may be understood,
        but they are not heeded.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There is more hope for a foolthan for someone who speaks without
        thinking.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A servant pampered from childhoodwill become a rebel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'An angry person starts fights;a hot-tempered person commits all kinds
        of sin.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Pride ends in humiliation,while humility brings honor.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you assist a thief, you only hurt yourself.You are sworn to tell
        the truth, but you dare not testify.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Fearing people is a dangerous trap,but trusting the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        means safety.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Many seek the ruler\u2019s favor,but justice comes from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Sayings of Agur
      content: '  The sayings of Agur son of Jakeh contain this message.[[COMMENT(0)]]I
        am weary, O God;I am weary and worn out, O God.[[COMMENT(1)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '30:1a '
        content: Or <b>son of Jakeh from Massa; </b>or <b>son of Jakeh, an oracle.</b>
      - number: '30:1b '
        content: The Hebrew can also be translated <b>The man declares this to Ithiel,
          / to Ithiel and to Ucal.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'I am too stupid to be human,and I lack common sense.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have not mastered human wisdom,nor do I know the Holy One.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who but God goes up to heaven and comes back down?Who holds the wind
        in his fists?Who wraps up the oceans in his cloak?Who has created the whole
        wide world?What is his name\u2014and his son\u2019s name?Tell me if you know!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Every word of God proves true.He is a shield to all who come to him
        for protection.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do not add to his words,or he may rebuke you and expose you as a
        liar.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O God, I beg two favors from you;let me have them before I die.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'First, help me never to tell a lie.Second, give me neither poverty
        nor riches!Give me just enough to satisfy my needs.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For if I grow rich, I may deny you and say, \u201CWho is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?\u201DAnd
        if I am too poor, I may steal and thus insult God\u2019s holy name.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Never slander a worker to the employer,or the person will curse you,
        and you will pay for it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Some people curse their fatherand do not thank their mother.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They are pure in their own eyes,but they are filthy and unwashed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They look proudly around,casting disdainful glances.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They have teeth like swordsand fangs like knives.They devour the
        poor from the earthand the needy from among humanity.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The leech has two suckersthat cry out, \u201CMore, more!\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]There
        are three things that are never satisfied\u2014no, four that never say, \u201CEnough!\u201D:  "
      comments:
      - number: '30:15 '
        content: "Hebrew <b>two daughters who cry out, \u201CGive, give!\u201D</b>"
    - title: 
      content: 'the grave,[[COMMENT(0)]]the barren womb,the thirsty desert,the blazing
        fire.  '
      comments:
      - number: '30:16 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Sheol.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "The eye that mocks a fatherand despises a mother\u2019s instructionswill
        be plucked out by ravens of the valleyand eaten by vultures.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There are three things that amaze me\u2014no, four things that I
        don\u2019t understand:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'how an eagle glides through the sky,how a snake slithers on a rock,how
        a ship navigates the ocean,how a man loves a woman.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "An adulterous woman consumes a man,then wipes her mouth and says,
        \u201CWhat\u2019s wrong with that?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There are three things that make the earth tremble\u2014no, four
        it cannot endure:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'a slave who becomes a king,an overbearing fool who prospers,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'a bitter woman who finally gets a husband,a servant girl who supplants
        her mistress.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There are four things on earth that are small but unusually wise:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Ants\u2014they aren\u2019t strong,but they store up food all summer.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Hyraxes[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014they aren\u2019t powerful,but they make
        their homes among the rocks.  "
      comments:
      - number: '30:26 '
        content: Or <b>Coneys, </b>or <b>Rock badgers.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Locusts\u2014they have no king,but they march in formation.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Lizards\u2014they are easy to catch,but they are found even in kings\u2019
        palaces.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There are three things that walk with stately stride\u2014no, four
        that strut about:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "the lion, king of animals, who won\u2019t turn aside for anything,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'the strutting rooster,the male goat,a king as he leads his army.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you have been a fool by being proud or plotting evil,cover your
        mouth in shame.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Sayings of King Lemuel
      content: '  The sayings of King Lemuel contain this message,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        which his mother taught him.  '
      comments:
      - number: '31:1 '
        content: 'Or <b>of Lemuel, king of Massa; </b>or <b>of King Lemuel, an oracle.</b>  '
    - title: 
      content: 'O my son, O son of my womb,O son of my vows,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'do not waste your strength on women,on those who ruin kings.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It is not for kings, O Lemuel, to guzzle wine.Rulers should not crave
        alcohol.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For if they drink, they may forget the lawand not give justice to
        the oppressed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Alcohol is for the dying,and wine for those in bitter distress.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let them drink to forget their povertyand remember their troubles
        no more.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Speak up for those who cannot speak for themselves;ensure justice
        for those being crushed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: A Wife of Noble Character
      content: 'Yes, speak up for the poor and helpless,and see that they get justice.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '  [[COMMENT(0)]]Who can find a virtuous and capable wife?She is more
        precious than rubies.  '
      comments:
      - number: '31:10 '
        content: '  Verses 10-31 comprise a Hebrew acrostic poem; each verse begins
          with a successive letter of the Hebrew alphabet.  '
    - title: 
      content: 'Her husband can trust her,and she will greatly enrich his life.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She brings him good, not harm,all the days of her life.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She finds wool and flaxand busily spins it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She is like a merchant\u2019s ship,bringing her food from afar.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "She gets up before dawn to prepare breakfast for her householdand
        plan the day\u2019s work for her servant girls.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She goes to inspect a field and buys it;with her earnings she plants
        a vineyard.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She is energetic and strong,a hard worker.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She makes sure her dealings are profitable;her lamp burns late into
        the night.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Her hands are busy spinning thread,her fingers twisting fiber.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She extends a helping hand to the poorand opens her arms to the needy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She has no fear of winter for her household,for everyone has warm[[COMMENT(0)]]
        clothes.  '
      comments:
      - number: '31:21 '
        content: As in Greek and Latin versions; Hebrew reads <b>scarlet.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'She makes her own bedspreads.She dresses in fine linen and purple
        gowns.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Her husband is well known at the city gates,where he sits with the
        other civic leaders.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She makes belted linen garmentsand sashes to sell to the merchants.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She is clothed with strength and dignity,and she laughs without fear
        of the future.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When she speaks, her words are wise,and she gives instructions with
        kindness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She carefully watches everything in her householdand suffers nothing
        from laziness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Her children stand and bless her.Her husband praises her:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThere are many virtuous and capable women in the world,but
        you surpass them all!\u201D  "
      comments: []
